Companies have understood that they need to follow the culture of the workplace in order not to become the next Uber. There has been a stir around the transportation company since a former employee wrote on his blog about a culture where employees are harassed and those who talk about problems are punished.
For startups like Glint, such omissions are an attractive business opportunity.
Corporate governance, regulation and compliance is a global industry worth more than $118.7 billion by 2020, according to the Let’s Talk Payments website.
Based in Denver, Colorado, Convercent is a start-up that helps companies detect and prevent inappropriate behavior. Interest in the company grew earlier this year when Uber’s reputation was hit hard.
